Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph chapter add

chapter add

Purpose:
  Insert a new chapter into an existing `.sdpub` chapter tree.

Usage:
  wikigraph chapter add <path> --stage planned [--title <title>] [--parent <id>] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph chapter add <path> --stage source [--title <title>] [--parent <id>] [--input <path>] --input-format <format> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Behavior:
  - `--stage planned` creates an empty chapter with no source, graph, or summary.
  - Planned chapters can be used as chapter directories, groups, or drafting placeholders.
  - `--stage source` creates a chapter and writes normalized source text.
  - Source input comes from `--input <path>` when provided, otherwise stdin.
  - Source input must not be empty or whitespace-only.
  - `--stage source` accepts only `txt` or `markdown` for `--input-format`.
  - Omitting `--title` creates an untitled planned chapter.
  - Omitting `--parent` adds the chapter at the top level.
  - `--parent <id>` adds the chapter under an existing chapter.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.

Output shape:
  Prints the new chapter status.
  The `Chapter: <id>` line is the new chapter id for later commands.

Typical next step:
  wikigraph queue add <path> --chapter <id> --task reading-graph --accept-cost

Examples:
  wikigraph chapter add book.sdpub --stage planned --title "Part I"
  wikigraph chapter add book.sdpub --stage source --title "Chapter 1" --input ./chapter.md --input-format markdown --parent 3

See also:
  - wikigraph chapter list --help
  - wikigraph chapter set-source --help
  - wikigraph help command
